# Security Notes

Genie is designed around a few core security principles:

- Only authorised Telegram users can issue commands.
- Access codes are validated before relay activation.
- Secrets should never be committed to source control.
- The relay remains inactive during fault conditions.
- Automatic restart protection prevents uncontrolled reboot loops.
- Status notifications help administrators detect abnormal behaviour quickly.

For deployments in production, it is recommended to:
- Store credentials securely.
- Rotate access codes periodically.
- Restrict physical access to the controller.
- Keep firmware and dependencies up to date.

